From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 10:35:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: ipq5332: Add CMN PLL node

Add the CMN PLL clock-controller node at offset 0x9b000 (same address
as IPQ5018) plus a ref_48mhz_clk fixed-clock providing the 48 MHz
reference that the on-board WiFi block feeds to the CMN PLL input
(matches IPQ9574's setup).

assigned-clock-rates-u64 is deliberately omitted: U-Boot already locks
the PLL at the right rate before Linux starts. The driver only needs
to register the fixed-rate output clocks; we don't want it to run a
reset+re-lock cycle while NSS / ethernet are mid-initialization later.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5332.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5332.dtsi
@@ -16,6 +16,12 @@
 	#size-cells = <2>;
 
 	clocks {
+		ref_48mhz_clk: ref-48mhz-clk {
+			compatible = "fixed-clock";
+			#clock-cells = <0>;
+			clock-frequency = <48000000>;
+		};
+
 		sleep_clk: sleep-clk {
 			compatible = "fixed-clock";
 			#clock-cells = <0>;
@@ -179,6 +185,22 @@
 			};
 		};
 
+		cmn_pll: clock-controller@9b000 {
+			compatible = "qcom,ipq5332-cmn-pll";
+			reg = <0x0009b000 0x800>;
+			clocks = <&ref_48mhz_clk>,
+				 <&gcc GCC_CMN_12GPLL_AHB_CLK>,
+				 <&gcc GCC_CMN_12GPLL_SYS_CLK>;
+			clock-names = "ref", "ahb", "sys";
+			#clock-cells = <1>;
+			/*
+			 * The CMN PLL is configured by U-Boot before Linux
+			 * starts; we deliberately omit assigned-clock-rates-u64
+			 * here so the driver only registers fixed-rate output
+			 * clocks and does not re-issue a PLL reset sequence.
+			 */
+		};
+
 		rng: rng@e3000 {
 			compatible = "qcom,prng-ee";
 			reg = <0x000e3000 0x1000>;
